Measuring the Read Noise¶

CCD Operation:¶

Notes: We obtained the darks by holding the lens cap over the CCD detector to remove any light from hitting it. We also used CCD Ops to tell the CCD to take Darks only during this part.

Gain¶

Notes: We did not take separate "light" exposures, though the mean of our longest "bright" exposure only reached ~14,000 counts

gain = [(F1+F2) - (B1+B2)] / [($\sigma$(F1-F2))$^2$ - ($\sigma$(B1-B2))$^2$]

def gain(b1, b2, f1, f2):
    f1 = np.array(f1, dtype='float')
    f2 = np.array(f2, dtype='float')
    b1 = np.array(b1, dtype='float')
    b2 = np.array(b2, dtype='float')
    top = (np.nanmedian(f1)+np.nanmedian(f2)) - (np.nanmedian(b1)+np.nanmedian(b2))
    bottom = np.std(f1-f2)**2 - np.std(b1-b2)**2
    return top / bottom
